description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like a varied, interesting and dynamic Acute Floor Rotational Post covering Balcombe ( Acute Assessment Unit) Pyecombe ( Respiratory and General Medicine) and the Emergency Department? We can also offer a 6 week bespoke placement during this rotation in ITU/HDU to gain your confidence and skills at looking after the acutely ill and deteriorating patient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will spend 6 months in each area being supported and developed by Senior Nursing staff and our dedicated Practice Educator. You will develop a broad overview and knowledge of General medicine and Emergency Nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you think this is an exciting opportunity that could give you a superb foundation to your nursing career then apply and join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are proud to be able to offer a variety of flexible working options and contracts. For further information please refer to the Flexible Working for Registered Nurses document which is attached to this advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamebDavid McKenna&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Acute Floor Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address david.mckenna4@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
